PN,16302
SC,0002
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1774455107
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 30 Mar to Wed 8 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure to the southwest of the
OL,7,FUK will likely be the dominant feature
OL,8,Ffor this period. This will lead to a
OL,9,Ffairly blocked pattern, with weather
OL,10,Ffronts rounding the high to affect
OL,11,Fnorthern parts at times, where wet and
OL,12,Fwindy weather can be expected. Further
OL,13,Fsouth, drier and more settled
OL,14,Fconditions are more likely, as frontal
OL,15,Fsystems weaken as they meet the high
OL,16,Fpressure. Through the period, high
OL,17,Fpressure is likely to spread across
OL,18,Fmuch of the UK leading to settled
OL,19,Fconditions developing more widely.
OL,20,FWhilst temperatures will be generally
OL,21,Fnear to or a little above average,
OL,22,Fsome colder interludes are possible,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fespecially in the north, where there
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fcould be some wintry showers at times.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1774455107
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 9 Apr to Thu 23 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure will likely be dominant
OL,7,Fat the start of this period. As such,
OL,8,Fplenty of dry weather seems most
OL,9,Flikely, but with changes in wind
OL,10,Fdirection leading to some quite marked
OL,11,Fdifferences in cloud amounts and
OL,12,Ftemperature from day to day. Moving
OL,13,Ffurther into April, there is a chance
OL,14,Fthat high pressure will become less
OL,15,Fdominant and thus there is a greater
OL,16,Fchance of more places seeing some rain
OL,17,Fand possible stronger winds from time
OL,18,Fto time. Overall, temperatures will
OL,19,Flikely be near to average.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
